+## Browser Capture Behavior
+
+The first browser connector captures public/local URLs through a direct HTTP request.
+
+| Mode | Behavior |
+|---|---|
+| `capture browser --url ...` | Fetches the URL and stores visible text as a memory record |
+| future Playwright connector | Uses a real browser session for authenticated pages and screenshots |
+
+Authenticated ChatGPT page capture is intentionally deferred until the Playwright/Chrome connector exists.
+
 ## Design Rule
 
 If a connector is fragile, keep it optional. The core should still work through manual capture and file import.
